gomodel:SYNGO_2871  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Effect of Caldendrin Overexpression and Deletion on Morphology of Dendritic Spines in Hippocampal Neurons\"\nFig.5: \"shRNA Knockdown of Caldendrin or Cortactin Abolishes BDNF-Induced Changes in Spine Density and Spine Size Potentiation\"\nFig.6: \"Caldendrin Regulates Actin and Cortactin Turnover in Spines\"\nFig.7: \"Lack of Caldendrin Causes Misarrangement of Spinous F-Actin at the Nanoscale Level\"\nFig.8: \"Caldendrin-Knockout Mice Show Severely Diminished CA1 LTP and Impaired Performance in Hippocampus-Specific Memory Task due to Impaired Activity-Dependent Spine Stabilization\". Experimental description: - Mouse: cald-/-\n- Overexpressed CABP1; Caldendrin is of rat species (traced back via blat analysis of seq TCCTGGCGGAGACAGCAGATA that only matches the rat genome)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
